OL,3,CCustomers 'will get compensation' say
OL,4,CSouth West Water after supply
OL,5,Cdisruption
OL,7,FResidents and businesses in and around
OL,8,FPlymouth are still waiting to find out
OL,9,Fhow much compensation they'll get - as
OL,10,Fwater supplies started to return to
OL,11,Fnormal.
OL,13,FSome people have faced three days
OL,14,Fwithout water, while a number of
OL,15,Fschools and businesses remain closed
OL,16,Fas a result of the ongoing problems.
OL,18,FAt its worst, up to 14,000 customers
OL,19,Fwere left without a water supply.
